<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1641: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Lisbon</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-04">December 4,
                                        1940</date>.<lb/>[Received December 4—4:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>843. For Long from Murphy.<note n="82" xml:id="d246fn82">Robert D.
                                    Murphy, Consul at Paris.</note> After thorough investigation of
                                facilities for the repatriation of destitute American citizens now
                                in France Wiley states that adequate space will be available from
                                Lisbon on steamers of American Export Line. Wiley states that
                                preliminary survey shows accommodations available as follows:
                                January 17th 65 persons; January 24th 30 persons; January 31st 50
                                persons; February 4th 150 persons. [Murphy.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>